description: This file contains source code implementing creation, initialization, and destruction functions for a 'Bree Cooked Page' object used within a BSP runtime engine, including object management routines such as create, remove, enroll objects, and initialize.

classes.name: BREE_COOKED_BSP_PAGE
classes.description: Structure representing the Bree Cooked Page object, including function pointers and internal data members like dynamic content flag and archived content pointer.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE BreeCreateCookedPageObj(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Factory function to create a new cooked page object, internally calls BreeCpoCreate.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE BreeCpoCreate(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Constructs and initializes a new Bree Cooked Page object, setting function pointers and creating internal structure.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BreeCpoRemove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Destroys the Bree Cooked Page object, freeing allocated memory if content is dynamic.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BreeCpoEnrollObjects(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Enrols necessary sub-objects or ancillary objects needed by the main object.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS BreeCpoInitialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes the object, setting functions and default member values.
